I"	<h1 id="custom-citizen-names">Custom Citizen Names</h1>

<p>Would you like to have citizen names in your own language? Then this is your page!<br />
Everything you have to change is in one file.
<br /></p>

<h2 id="procedure">Procedure</h2>
<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Locate the file <em>minecolonies-server.toml</em>.<br /></p>

    <p>For servers:<br /></p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> (minecraftServerFolder)/world/serverconfig/minecolonies-server.toml
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p>For local worlds:<br /></p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> (minecraftFolder)/saves/(NameOfYourWorld)/serverconfig/minecolonies-server.toml
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Edit</p>

    <p>You can use the official language templates we provide here or you can edit at your own risk. If you decide to edit, don’t forget to make a copy of the file first and follow the current structure.
 <br /></p>
    <ul>
 <li>Edit with a text editor, like Notepad.</li>
 <li>The file must have the same name.</li>
 </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Run Minecraft client/server and enjoy!</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p><br /></p>

